text: Swedish Volleyball Federation () is a special sports association for volleyball in Sweden. It was established on 3 June 1961 It was appointed into the Swedish Sports Confederation in 1961. It is based in Solna. It represents Sweden with national teams like the Sweden men's national volleyball team and the Sweden women's national volleyball team. ==References== Category:1961 establishments in Sweden Category:Sports organizations of Sweden Category:Sports governing bodies in Europe Category:Volleyball organizations
